{"id": 4697, "title": "Ticket #4697: default JOB_RENICE_INCREMENT different in std uni and vanilla", "description": "<blockquote>\nHTCondor has the ability to use the Unix system call 'nice' to lower the unix process priority of a job.  In the past, the idea was that on a really slow cpu, perhaps on a Unix with a poorly designed scheduler, this would help the startd have enough cycles to manage an out of control job.  There is a knob that controls how much \"nice\"-ness to give job, called\n\n<p>JOB_RENICE_INCREMENT\n\n</p><p>it looks like there's an inconsistency in HTCondor where if this parameter is not defined, the vanilla universe defaults it to 10, and the standard universe starter defaults it to 0.\n\n</p><p>We will make this default to 0 everywhere.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Nov-20 09:34:04 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW:</strong> looks good</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Nov-20 11:17</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=41704\">[41704]</a></span>: minor 8.2.5 version history item edit <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"defer\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4697\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4697'); return false;\" title=\"default JOB_RENICE_INCREMENT different in std uni and vanilla\">#4697</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Nov-04 13:21</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=41580\">[41580]</a></span>: Version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"defer\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4